atextbtxt2rdacontent  aunmediatedbn2rdamedia  avolumebnc2rdacarrier1 aPublicación de DHHS (NIOSH) ;vnúmero 2013-149 (Sp2013)  aTitle from cover.  a"Mayo 2013."  aThe information in this publication is based on NIOSH supported research; Nail Gun Safety: A Guide for Construction Contractors (NIOSH Publication No. 2011-202/OSHA Publication No. 3459-8-11); and focus group discussions with residential building subcontractors, safety specialists and workers. New nail gun users must receive safety training, not just a copy of this publication. Safety training requirements are described in detail in Nail Gun Safety: A Guide for Construction Contractors and can be viewed and printed or downloaded from www.cdc.gov/niosh/docs/2011-202.  aLa información en esta publicaciónn está basada en investigación apoyada por NIOSH; the Seguridad con las pistolas de clavos : guía para los contratistas del sector de la construcción [Nail Gun Safety, A Guide for Construction Contractors] (publicación de NIOSH núm. 2011-202 (Sp2012)/publicación de la OSHA núm. 3459-8-11); y discusiones en grupos de enfoque con subcontratistas de la construcción residencial, especialistas enseguridad y trabajadores. Los nuevos usuarios de pistolas de clavos deben recibir instrucción en seguridad, no solamente una copia de esta publicación. Los requisitos para la instrucción en seguridad están descritos en detalle en Nail Gun Safety: A Guide for Construction Contractors y pueden ser vistos o impresos o descargados de www.cdc.gov/spanish/niosh/docs/2011-202_sp.  aPrint format not distributed to depository libraries.  aLibro de historietas que ilustran la necesidad para el entrenamiento de seguridad en el uso de pistolas de clavos.  aComic book illustrating the need for safety training in the use of nail guns.  aAlso available via the World Wide Web as an Acrobat .pdf file (5.3 MB, 12 p.). 0aAccidentsxPrevention. 0aConstruction industry. 0aConstruction workers. 0aPneumatic nailers. 0aSafety education. 0aBuilding tradesxEmployees.2 aNational Institute for Occupational Safety and Health,eissuing body.1https://id.oclc.org/worldcat/entity/E39QQPVp7PrkyBPgwpKQK4wvTR08iEnglish language version:aNational Institute for Occupational Safety and Health.tStraight talk about nail gun safety.dCincinnati, OH] : Department of Health and Human Services, Centers for Disease Control and Prevention, National Institute for Occupational Safety and Health, 2013.kDHHS publication ; no. (NIOSH) 2013-149w(OCoLC)4658980808iOnline version:tPlática directa sobre seguridad con pistolas de clavosw(OCoLC)109803477208iBased uponaNational Institute for Occupational Safety and Health.tNail gun safety : a guide for construction contractors.d[Cincinnati, OH] : Department of Health and Human Services, Centers for Disease Control and Prevention, National Institute for Occupational Safety and Health; [Washington, DC] : Department of Labor, Occupational Safety and Health Administration, 2011.k(DHHS (NIOSH) publication ; no. 2011-202) (OSHA publication ; no. 3459-8-11)w(OCoLC)756456772 0aDHHS publication ;vno. (NIOSH) 2013-149 (Sp2013)  aC0bGPO  abc48 20260416  abcb77 20191002  abcb77 20190422b2019042202299ces a2200517 i 00109959020260409083434.0s x        f0    0aj canzncr |||||||||||190523c19uu9999dcubg     c  f  0   eng c  a20192317501 aab500000  a(OCoLC)1102319397  aGPObengerdacGPOdGPOdOCLdGPO  apcc  an-us-ncan-us-va  aGPOO  a3902bB55  a06510 aI 29.6:B 62/3/1 aUnited States.bNational Park Service,ecartographer.0http://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/n7902280910aBlue Ridge Parkway /cNational Park Service, U.S. Department of the Interior.1 iPanel title:aBlue Ridge Parkway, North Carolina/Virginia  aScale approximately 1:500,000. 1aWashington, D.C. :bNational Park Service  amaps :bboth sides, color ;c114 x 21 cm, folded to 10 x 21 cm  aIrregular  acartographic imagebcri2rdaconte